parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking and disintegration of the dashboard can cause sharp plastic projectiles to fly into the air if the airbag deploys, potentially causing injuries to occupants. Additionally, the broken pieces can fall into the air vents, causing electrical problems and potentially leading to a fire.
symptoms: with pieces breaking off and falling into the air vents or onto the floor. The cracks can be straight or jagged
and the dashboard may make a loud popping or cracking noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause structural damage, leading to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, or even fatalities.
symptoms: The frame is rusting or corroding
with large areas of metal disintegrating. The rust can be severe
causing the frame to weaken and potentially collapse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the pinion nut can cause the drive shaft to fall off, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
The failure of the drive shaft can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
The failure of the rear axle can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
The failure of the clutch interlock safety switch can cause unintended vehicle movement, leading to accidents and injuries.
Transmission and powertrain issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
The cracking and disintegration of the dashboard can cause electrical failures, airbag malfunctions, and obstruct the driver's view, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: and disintegration; electrical failures; airbag light on; obstructed view.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signals can cause accidents or near-misses, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intentions.
symptoms: Intermittent turn signal failure; right turn signal flashes when left turn signal is engaged; left turn signal flashes when right turn signal is engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HVAC system can cause discomfort, distraction, and decreased visibility, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Blower motor failure; blend door and actuator failure; no heat or air conditioning; popping sound when turning on heat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of problems, including loss of power, stalling, and accidents.
symptoms: Loss of power; stalling; gauges not working; ABS
and airbag lights on; no controls for defroster.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lockup of the steering column can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Steering column locks up; key slides out of ignition; vehicle stalls or dies.
